      <section id="overview">
        <h1>Overview</h1>
        <p>Welcome to the NodCord documentation. NodCord is a versatile and powerful Discord bot framework that simplifies the process of creating and managing your own Discord bots.</p>
        <p>With NodCord, you can easily set up, configure, and deploy bots that interact with Discord servers, providing a seamless integration experience. This documentation will guide you through the installation, configuration, and usage of NodCord, along with detailed information about its API.</p>
      </section>
      <section id="installation">
        <h2>Installation</h2>
        <p>To install NodCord, ensure you have Node.js and npm installed on your system. Run the following command to install NodCord:</p>
        <pre><code>npm install nodcord</code></pre>
        <p>Once installed, you can start building your bot with ease using the features provided by NodCord.</p>
      </section>
      <section id="configuration">
        <h2>Configuration</h2>
        <p>After installation, you need to configure NodCord to work with your Discord bot. Create a <code>.env</code> file in your project directory and add the following environment variables:</p>
        <pre><code>DISCORD_TOKEN=your_discord_token_here
BOT_PREFIX=!</code></pre>
        <p>These variables will be used by NodCord to authenticate your bot with Discord and to set the command prefix for the bot's interactions.</p>
      </section>
      <section id="usage">
        <h2>Usage</h2>
        <p>To start using NodCord, create an <code>index.js</code> file and add the following code to initialize your bot:</p>
        <pre><code>const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('nodcord');
const client = new Client({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds, GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages] });

client.on('ready', () => {
  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);
});

client.login(process.env.DISCORD_TOKEN);</code></pre>
        <p>This script sets up a basic bot that logs in to Discord using the token you provided and outputs a message when it is successfully connected.</p>
      </section>
      <section id="api">
        <h2>API Reference</h2>
        <p>NodCord provides a comprehensive API for interacting with Discord. Here are some of the main methods:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>client.on(event, listener)</code> - Listens for a specific event.</li>
          <li><code>client.login(token)</code> - Logs in to Discord with the provided token.</li>
          <li><code>client.user.setActivity(activity)</code> - Sets the bot's activity status.</li>
          <li><code>client.guilds.cache</code> - Accesses the cache of guilds (servers) the bot is part of.</li>
          <li><code>client.channels.cache</code> - Accesses the cache of channels within the bot's guilds.</li>
          <li><code>client.users.cache</code> - Accesses the cache of users that the bot has interacted with.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For more detailed information, refer to the full API documentation included in the NodCord package or visit the official NodCord GitHub repository.</p>
      </section>
      <section id="faq">
