        <p>Here are some frequently asked questions about NodCord:</p>
        <h3>What is NodCord?</h3>
        <p>NodCord is a framework for creating Discord bots with ease. It provides a robust API and tools to help developers build and manage bots quickly.</p>
        <h3>How do I install NodCord?</h3>
        <p>To install NodCord, run the command <code>npm install nodcord</code> in your Node.js project.</p>
        <h3>Where can I find more information about the API?</h3>
        <p>The API reference is included in this documentation and can also be found in the NodCord GitHub repository, where you can access the full list of available methods and features.</p>
        <h3>How do I configure my bot?</h3>
        <p>Configuration is done using a <code>.env</code> file where you define your Discord token and bot prefix. This file should be placed in the root directory of your project.</p>
      </section>
